    "We note that PoLAR incurs computational overhead during fine-tuning compared to LoRA, due to the landing field computation and the additional r × r matrix Θ t.",
    "As already mentioned, this runtime overhead compares favorably to a classical Riemannian treatment based on retractions (see Section 4.4).",
